<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="281" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,908,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name “rondonia” refer to the Brazilian state of 
<collectingRegion box="[964,1073,908,933]" country="Brazil" name="Rondonia" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Rondonia</collectingRegion>
, from where the 
<typeStatus box="[1283,1381,908,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1436,151,1040]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,496,980,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
This species is known from the 
<typeStatus box="[864,912,981,1005]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">type</typeStatus>
locality and to 
<collectingRegion box="[1090,1143,980,1004]" country="Brazil" name="Para" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Pará</collectingRegion>
, in the Caxiuanã National Forest (
<geoCoordinate box="[237,366,1016,1040]" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="281" precision="15" value="-1.7372222">01°44'14&quot;S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[378,523,1015,1040]" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="281" precision="15" value="-51.456944">51°27′25″W</geoCoordinate>
).
</paragraph>
